name: INStartVideoCallIntentResponseCode
desc: Constants indicating the status of the response.

items.name: case unspecified
items.desc: Your app can’t provide a more specific response.

items.name: case ready
items.desc: You’re ready to handle the intent.

items.name: case continueInApp
items.desc: Your extension is ready to transfer control to the app so that your app can place the call.

items.name: case failure
items.desc: You were unable to initiate the call.

items.name: case failureRequiringAppLaunch
items.desc: The user must launch your app to initiate the call.

items.name: case failureAppConfigurationRequired
items.desc: The user must perform additional configuration steps before initiating a call is possible.

items.name: case failureCallingServiceNotAvailable
items.desc: Your app’s calling service isn’t currently available.

items.name: case failureContactNotSupportedByApp
items.desc: Your app can’t use the specified contact to place the call.

items.name: case failureInvalidNumber
items.desc: The specified number doesn’t support video calls.
